HEADWORD: Summity
<hw>Sum"mit*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>summitas</ets>, fr. <ets>summus</ets> highest: cf. F.
<ets>sommit⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See <er>Sum</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The height or top of anything.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The utmost degree; perfection.</def>
